11/07/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The second, bilateral phase of EU screening of Croatia's legislation under the Chapter on Consumers and Health Protection of the acquis wrapped up in Brussels on Tuesday (11 July). 
During the two-day talks, Croatia briefed European Commission (EC) negotiators on the level of harmonisation between domestic legislation and that of the EU.
On Monday, the first, analytical phase of the screening process under the External Relations chapter was held in Brussels. 
The second stage is scheduled for mid-September. 
(HRT - 10/07/06)
